05.\n* Miles, Barry. ''William Burroughs: El Hombre Invisible, A Portrait''. New York: Hyperion, 1992.\n* Sargeant, Jack. \"Naked Lens: Beat Cinema\" New York: Soft Skull, 2009 (third edition).\n* Schneiderman, Davis and Philip Walsh. ''Retaking the Universe: William S. Burroughs in the Age of Globalization''. London: Pluto Press, 2004.\n* Stevens, Michael. ''The Road to Interzone: Reading William S. Burroughs Reading''. suicide press, Archer City, Texas, 2009.\n* Weidner, Chad. ''The Green Ghost: William Burroughs and the Ecological Mind''. Carbondale, IL: Southern Illinois University Press, 2016.\n* Wills, David S. ''Scientologist! William S. Burroughs and the Weird Cult''. Beatdom Books, London, 2013.\n\n===Archival sources===\n* [http://archives.nypl.org/brg/19345 William S. Burroughs papers] (17 linear feet - 94 boxes) are held by the Berg Collection of the [[New York Public Library]].\n* [http://findingaids.cul.columbia.edu/ead/nnc-rb/ldpd_4078569/ William Seward Burroughs Papers, 1957\u20131976] (2 linear feet) are held in the [[Columbia University Libraries]].\n* [http://library.osu.edu/finding-aids/rarebooks/burroughs40.php William S. Burroughs Papers, SPEC.CMS.40] (ca. 1945-ca. 1984, 55 boxes plus additions) are held in the Ohio State University Libraries.\n* [http://library.osu.edu/finding-aids/rarebooks/burroughs85.php William S. Burroughs Papers, SPEC.CMS.85]  (ca. 1945-ca. 1984, 6 boxes) are held in the Ohio State University Libraries.\n* [http://library.osu.edu/finding-aids/rarebooks/burroughs87.php William S. Burroughs Papers, SPEC.CMS.87]  (ca. 1945-ca. 1984, 58 boxes) are held in the Ohio State University Libraries.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20141204173531/http://library.osu.edu/finding-aids/rarebooks/burroughs90.php William S. Burroughs Papers, SPEC.CMS.90]  (ca. 1945-ca. 1984, 29 boxes) are held in the Ohio State University Libraries.\n* [http://findingaids.library.emory.edu/documents/burroughs1192/ William S. Burroughs collection] (3 linear feet) are held in the Manuscript, Archives, and Rare Book Library at [[Emory University]].\n* [http://hdl.handle.net/10407/5017064884 William S. Burroughs Collection, MS 63] and [http://hdl.handle.net/10407/6313993218 James Grauerholz Collection of William S. Burroughs, MS 319], are held at the [http://spencer.lib.ku.edu Kenneth Spencer Research Library], University of Kansas\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20120622160831/http://cstl-cla.semo.edu/gurnow/burroughs/main.htm William S. Burroughs Internet Database], edited by postmodern American scholar Michael Gurnow, hosted on the servers of [[Southeast Missouri State University]] from 2000-2012.\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20170504233852/http://thephotographersgallery.org.uk/the-photography-of-william-s-burroughs], Taking Shots: The Photography of William S. Burroughs, The Photographers' Gallery exhibition website.\n* [https://vimeo.com/search?q=The+Photographers%27+Gallery+Burroughs], William S. Burroughs and Photography Lecture Series\n\n==External links==\n{{external links|date=September 2018}}\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n\n* {{IMDb name|0123221}}\n* {{Isfdb name|id=338|name=William S. Burroughs}}\n* {{cite journal |url = http://www.theparisreview.org/interviews/4424/the-art-of-fiction-no-36-william-s-burroughs |title = William S. Burroughs, The Art of Fiction No. 36 |journal = The Paris Review |volume = Fall 1965 |issue = 35 |author = Conrad Knickerbocker |date = Fall 1965 }}\n* [http://realitystudio.org/ RealityStudio] fan site with texts, community, scholarship, criticism\n* William S. Burroughs audio documentary narrated by Iggy Pop [http://www.openculture.com/2015/02/william-s-burroughs-audio-documentary-narrated-by-iggy-pop.html]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20050215145758/http://cstl-cla.semo.edu/gurnow/burroughs/main.htm William S. Burroughs Internet Database] at [[Southeast Missouri State University]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150206154803/http://nakedlunch.org/ International festivities for 50th anniversary] of ''Naked Lunch''\n* [http://www.beatbookcovers.com/burroughs A gallery of Burroughs book cover designs]\n* [http://www.vlib.us/beats/malcolmmcneill.html Artist Malcolm McNeill: On Beat Writer William Burroughs], Interview by George Laughead, August 2007\n* [http://www.dhalgren.com/Doom/ch10.html Doom Patrols: 10. WILLIAM BURROUGHS by Steven Shaviro]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20091012165539/http://www.beatdom.com/tom_waits.htm William Burroughs and Tom Waits]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090907012212/http://www.researchpubs.com/books/bgtgexc1.php Interview] excerpt from [[RE/Search]]\n* [http://www.vlib.us/beats/shootingjoan.html Shooting Joan Burroughs by George Laughead]\n* [http://www.vlib.us/beats/wsbginsberg.html Allen Ginsberg & William S. Burroughs, Last Public Appearance] November 2, 1996 Lawrence, KS\n* [http://ebsn.eu/ European Beat Studies Network]\n* [https://www.pbs.org/independentlens/william-s-burroughs/ ''William S. Burroughs: A Man Within''] site for [[Independent Lens]] on [[PBS]]\n* {{IMDb title|1466072|William S. Burroughs: A Man Within}}\n* [http://www.sensitiveskinmagazine.com/william-s-burroughs-interview/ William S. Burroughs interviewed by Allen Ginsberg], March 1992 in Lawrence, Kansas, from ''[[Sensitive Skin (magazine)|Sensitive Skin]]'' magazine #8, published April 2012\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iTgw5kZvTuY Burroughs on Bowery], a film by Marc Olmsted of Burroughs in New York City in 1977\n* [http://escholarship.org/uc/item/8mq028p5 Anything but Routine: A Selectively Annotated Bibliography of William S. Burroughs v 2.0] by Brian E.C. Schottlaender, UC San Diego, 2010\n* [http://www.thisamericanlife.org/radio-archives/episode/546/burroughs-101 Burroughs 101] by [[This American Life]], January 30, 2015\n* [https://www.aaa.si.edu/collections/william-burroughs-and-brion-gysin-writings-17446 A finding aid to the William Burroughs and Brion Gysin writings, 1963-1973, 1997 in the Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution]\n* {{findagrave|6201607}}\n\n{{William S. Burroughs| state=expanded}}\n{{Allen Ginsberg}}\n{{Jack Kerouac| state=collapsed}}\n{{Chaos magic series}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Burroughs, William S}}\n[[Category:William S. Burroughs| ]]\n[[Category:20th-century American criminals]]\n[[Category:20th-century American novelists]]\n[[Category:20th-century American painters]]\n[[Category:20th-century American poets]]\n[[Category:20th-century American short story writers]]\n[[Category:1914 births]]\n[[Category:1997 deaths]]\n[[Category:American erotica writers]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in France]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in Mexico]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in Morocco]]\n[[Category:American expatriates in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:American male novelists]]\n[[Category:American male painters]]\n[[Category:American male poets]]\n[[Category:American male short story writers]]\n[[Category:American occultists]]\n[[Category:American outlaws]]\n[[Category:American people convicted of manslaughter]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American science fiction writers]]\n[[Category:American spoken word artists]]\n[[Category:Beat Generation writers]]\n[[Category:Bisexual men]]\n[[Category:Bisexual writers]]\n[[Category:Burials at Bellefontaine Cemetery]]\n[[Category:Chaos magicians]]\n[[Category:Chevaliers of the Ordre des Arts et des Lettres]]\n[[Category:Criminals from Missouri]]\n[[Category:Critics of Scientology]]\n[[Category:Drug policy reform activists]]\n[[Category:ESP-Disk artists]]\n[[Category:Former Scientologists]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Heroin]]\n[[Category:LGBT novelists]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Kansas]]\n[[Category:LGBT people from Missouri]]\n[[Category:LGBT poets]]\n[[Category:LGBT writers from the United States]]\n[[Category:Members of the American Academy of Arts and Letters]]\n[[Category:Obscenity controversies in liter