{"title_page": "Jake Pavelka", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n|name=Jake Pavelka\n|image = Jake Pavelka & Vienna Girardi 2010.jpg\n|caption = Jake Pavelka and Vienna Girardi (2010)\n|birth_name= Jacob Lynn Pavelka\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1978|1|27}}\n|birth_place=[[Dallas, Texas]]\n|othername= Jake Landrum\n|height= 1.78 m\n|occupation= [[Aviator|Pilot]], television personality, model, triathlete\n|years_active = 1999\u20132000; 2009\u2013present\n|partner = Vienna Girardi, Meghan Jones, Tanya Douglas, Ashley Ann Vickers; Morgan Matlock \n|parents= Sallie Lanell Mack Pavelka (Mother), James Lynn Pavelka (Father)\n|relatives= Jason Pavelka (brother), Matthew Pavelka (brother), [[Jessie Pavelka]] (cousin)\n}}\n\n'''Jacob Lynn \"Jake\" Pavelka''' (born January 27, 1978) is an [[United States|American]] television personality who appeared on six [[reality TV]] programs, most notably ''[[The Bachelor (US TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.\n\n== Early life and career ==\nPavelka was born in [[Dallas, Texas]] to Sallie Lanell ([[n\u00e9e]] Mack),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/the-new-bachelor-jake-pavelka-second-chance-at-love-vol-72-no-17/ |title=The New Bachelor Jake Pavelka Second Chance at Love |last=Rizzo |first=Monica |work=People |date=October 26, 2009 |access-date=March 1, 2019}}</ref> a nurse, and James Lynn Pavelka. He is the middle child of three sons. His brothers, Jason and Matthew, are both married. He has two nephews. Pavelka grew up in [[Denton, Texas]] and he started taking flying lessons when he was twelve. He eventually worked as a pilot for [[Atlantic Southeast Airlines]], and under the name of Jake Landrum, acted in several television commercials and programs produced in the Dallas area.<ref name=TVG>{{cite news|title=Jake Pavelka Biography |publisher=TV Guide Online |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jake-pavelka/bio/298929 | accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref> Pavelka is a cousin of fitness model, television presenter, actor and personal trainer [[Jessie Pavelka]]. Pavelka participates in [[triathlons]] and has been active in fitness throughout his life.\n\n== Reality television ==\n\nPavelka first appeared as a contestant in 2009, in the fifth season of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] reality show ''[[The Bachelorette]]''. He was eliminated by Canadian [[Jillian Harris]] before hometowns, but was brought back by the network to star in the [[The Bachelor (season 14)|14th season of its series ''The Bachelor'']] in 2010. The program's run ended with Pavelka proposing marriage to contestant [[Vienna Girardi]] in the March 2010 finale.<ref name=TVG /> The couple split up in June 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Vienna-Split-1019818.aspx|title=The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka and Vienna Girardi Split|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the end of ''The Bachelor'', Pavelka was named as one of the celebrity contestants for the tenth season of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|Dancing with the Stars]]''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Joyce Eng |title=Dancing\u2019s Jake Pavelka: I Feel Dumb Every Day in Rehearsal | publisher=Seattle Post-Intelligencer |date=March 25, 2010 |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/tvguide/417403_dancing25.html | accessdate=2010-03-30}}{{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> He and his partner [[Chelsie Hightower]] were the fifth to be eliminated, in April 2010. In July 2011, Pavelka was a contestant on the second season of ''[[Bachelor Pad]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bierly |first=Mandi |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/06/13/bachelor-pad-cast-season-2/ |title=Official 'Bachelor Pad' cast revealed - EXCLUSIVE &#124; Inside TV &#124; EW.com |publisher=Insidetv.ew.com |date=2011-06-13 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref> He was also a contestant on [[VH1]]'s 2011 reality series ''[[Famous Food]]'', and appeared on a September 2011 episode of [[The CW]]'s reality show ''[[H8R]]''.  In 2014, he was a contestant on ''Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodnetwork.com/rachael-vs-guy-celebrity-cook-off/index.html|title=Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off|publisher=|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> On May 23, 2016, he appeared as a surprise guest on the ''Bachelorette'' with [[JoJo Fletcher]].\n\n== Other work==\nIn June 2010, Pavelka was scheduled to guest-star on an episode of ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'' as Toby Devlin, contestant on a fictional reality dating show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Pavelka-Diva-1019583.aspx|title=Jake Pavelka to Play a Bachelor on Drop Dead Diva|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref>\nOn January 14, 2011, Pavelka guest-starred on ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Bachelors-Jake-Pavelka-1025792.aspx |title=The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka to Guest-Star on The Bold and the Beautiful |publisher=TVGuide.com |accessdate=November 19, 2010}}</ref>\n\nFrom February to March 2012, Pavelka was a celebrity guest host at the [[Chippendales]] show in [[Las Vegas Strip|Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/which_hunky_bachelor_star_joining/292723 |title=Which Hunky Bachelor Star Is Joining Chippendales |publisher=E! Online |date=2012-02-08 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]''\n| Young Cordell Walker\n| \n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[The President's Man]]''\n| Young Joshua McCord \n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[The Bachelorette]]''\n| Himself \n| [[The Bachelorette (season 5)|Season 5]] contestant\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Bachelor (U.S. TV series)|The Bachelor]]''\n| Himself \n| Starring role\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''\n| Himself \n| [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|Season 10]] contestant\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]''\n| Toby \n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Party Girl Plus One''\n| Bryce Wharton Powell III\n| \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Bachelor Pad]]''\n| Himself \n| Contestant \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Famous Food]]''\n| Himself \n| Contestant \n|-\n| 2011\u20132014\n| ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''\n| Kyle the Pilot\n| Recurring guest star\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Burning Love (web series)|Burning Love]]''\n| Jeff\n| web series\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off]]''\n| Himself\n|7th Place \n|-\n|2016\n| ''[[The Bachelorette]]''\n| Himself\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb name|0485023}}\n*[https://www.youtube.com/user/jakepavelka1/ Jake Pavelka's Official YouTube]\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Succession box|title=''[[The Bachelor (US TV series)|The Bachelor]]''|before=[[Jason Mesnick]]|after=[[Brad Womack]]|years=[[The Bachelor (season 14)|Season 14]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Bachelor}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pavelka, Jake}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:People from Dallas]]\n[[Category:Aviators from Texas]]\n[[Category:Embry\u2013Riddle Aeronautical University alumni]]\n[[Category:People from Denton, Texas]]\n[[Category:Players of American football from Texas]]\n[[Category:Atlantic Southeast Airlines]]\n[[Category:People from Daytona Beach, Florida]]\n[[Category:Male models from Texas]]\n[[Category:American male erotic dancers]]\n[[Category:American male triathletes]]\n[[Category:American aerospace engineers]]\n[[Category:American male child actors]]\n[[Category:American people of Czech descent]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Texas]]\n[[Category:University of North Texas alumni]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from the Dallas\u2013Fort Worth metroplex]]\n[[Category:Bachelor Nation contestants]]\n[[Category:American flight instructors]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person\n|name=Jake Pavelka\n|image = Jake Pavelka & Vienna Girardi 2010.jpg\n|caption = Jake Pavelka and Vienna Girardi (2010)\n|birth_name= Jacob Lynn Pavelka\n|birth_date={{Birth date and age|1978|1|27}}\n|birth_place=[[Dallas, Texas]]\n|othername= Jake Landrum\n|height= 1.78 m\n|occupation= [[Aviator|Pilot]], television personality, model, triathlete\n|years_active = 1999\u20132000; 2009\u2013present\n|partner = Vienna Girardi, Meghan Jones, Tanya Douglas, Ashley Ann Vickers; Morgan Matlock \n|parents= Sallie Lanell Mack Pavelka (Mother), James Lynn Pavelka (Father)\n|relatives= Jason Pavelka (brother), Matthew Pavelka (brother), [[Jessie Pavelka]] (cousin)\n}}\n\n'''Jacob Lynn \"Jake\" Pavelka''' (born January 27, 1978) is an [[United States|American]] television personality who appeared on six [[reality TV]] programs, most notably ''[[The Bachelor (US TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.\n\n== Early life and career ==\nPavelka was born in [[Dallas, Texas]] to Sallie Lanell ([[n\u00e9e]] Mack),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/archive/the-new-bachelor-jake-pavelka-second-chance-at-love-vol-72-no-17/ |title=The New Bachelor Jake Pavelka Second Chance at Love |last=Rizzo |first=Monica |work=People |date=October 26, 2009 |access-date=March 1, 2019}}</ref> a nurse, and James Lynn Pavelka. He is the middle child of three sons. His brothers, Jason and Matthew, are both married. He has two nephews. Pavelka grew up in [[Denton, Texas]] and he started taking flying lessons when he was twelve. He eventually worked as a pilot for [[Atlantic Southeast Airlines]], and under the name of Jake Landrum, acted in several television commercials and programs produced in the Dallas area.<ref name=TVG>{{cite news|title=Jake Pavelka Biography |publisher=TV Guide Online |url=http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jake-pavelka/bio/298929 | accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref> Pavelka is a cousin of fitness model, television presenter, actor and personal trainer [[Jessie Pavelka]]. Pavelka participates in [[triathlons]] and has been active in fitness throughout his life.\n\n== Reality television ==\n\nPavelka first appeared as a contestant in 2009, in the fifth season of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] reality show ''[[The Bachelorette]]''. He was eliminated by Canadian [[Jillian Harris]] before hometowns, but was brought back by the network to star in the [[The Bachelor (season 14)|14th season of its series ''The Bachelor'']] in 2010. The program\u2019s run ended with Pavelka proposing marriage to contestant [[Vienna Girardi]] in the March 2010 finale.<ref name=TVG /> The couple split up in June 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Vienna-Split-1019818.aspx|title=The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka and Vienna Girardi Split|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the end of ''The Bachelor'', Pavelka was named as one of the celebrity contestants for the tenth season of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|Dancing with the Stars]]''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Joyce Eng |title=Dancing\u2019s Jake Pavelka: I Feel Dumb Every Day in Rehearsal | publisher=Seattle Post-Intelligencer |date=March 25, 2010 |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/tvguide/417403_dancing25.html | accessdate=2010-03-30}}{{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> He and his partner [[Chelsie Hightower]] were the fifth to be eliminated, in April 2010. In July 2011, Pavelka was a contestant on the second season of ''[[Bachelor Pad]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bierly |first=Mandi |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/06/13/bachelor-pad-cast-season-2/ |title=Official 'Bachelor Pad' cast revealed - EXCLUSIVE &#124; Inside TV &#124; EW.com |publisher=Insidetv.ew.com |date=2011-06-13 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref> He was also a contestant on [[VH1]]'s 2011 reality series ''[[Famous Food]]'', and appeared on a September 2011 episode of [[The CW]]'s reality show ''[[H8R]]''.  In 2014, he was a contestant on ''Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodnetwork.com/rachael-vs-guy-celebrity-cook-off/index.html|title=Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off|publisher=|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> On May 23, 2016, he appeared as a surprise guest on the ''Bachelorette'' with [[JoJo Fletcher]].\n\n== Other work==\nIn June 2010, Pavelka was scheduled to guest-star on an episode of ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'' as Toby Devlin, contestant on a fictional reality dating show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Pavelka-Diva-1019583.aspx|title=Jake Pavelka to Play a Bachelor on Drop Dead Diva|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref>\nOn January 14, 2011, Pavelka guest-starred on ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Bachelors-Jake-Pavelka-1025792.aspx |title=The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka to Guest-Star on The Bold and the Beautiful |publisher=TVGuide.com |accessdate=November 19, 2010}}</ref>\n\nFrom February to March 2012, Pavelka was a celebrity guest host at the [[Chippendales]] show in [[Las Vegas Strip|Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/which_hunky_bachelor_star_joining/292723 |title=Which Hunky Bachelor Star Is Joining Chippendales |publisher=E! Online |date=2012-02-08 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1999\n| ''[[Walker, Texas Ranger]]''\n| Young Cordell Walker\n| \n|-\n| 2000\n| ''[[The President's Man]]''\n| Young Joshua McCord \n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[The Bachelorette]]''\n| Himself \n| [[The Bachelorette (season 5)|Season 5]] contestant\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[The Bachelor (U.S. TV series)|The Bachelor]]''\n| Himself \n| Starring role\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''\n| Himself \n| [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|Season 10]] contestant\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]''\n| Toby \n| \n|-\n| 2010\n| ''Party Girl Plus One''\n| Bryce Wharton Powell III\n| \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Bachelor Pad]]''\n| Himself \n| Contestant \n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[Famous Food]]''\n| Himself \n| Contestant \n|-\n| 2011\u20132014\n| ''[[The Bold and the B