{"title_page": "55 metres", "text_new": "'''55 metres''' is a [[Sprint (running)|sprint]] event in [[track and field]]. It is a relatively uncommon non-championship event for indoor track and field.\n\nThe history of the event lies in the [[60-yard dash]], which roughly equates to 55 metres. For this reason, the event is most popular in countries which use or have used [[imperial measurements]], especially the [[United States]]. Unlike the [[50 metres]] and [[60 metres]] running events, the 55 metres is not an [[IAAF]] recognised event.<ref>[http://www.iaaf.org/statistics/records/inout=I/disctype=0/detail.html IAAF records]. [[IAAF]]. Retrieved on 2009-01-05.</ref>\n\n==All-time top 25==\n''Indoor results only.  Hand-timed results are excluded''\n<br>\n*A = affected by altitude\n\n===Men===\n*Correct as of December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=All-time men's best 55m|url=http://www.tilastopaja.net/db/allt30.php?Sex=1&Event=20&Age=99&Ind=1|publisher=tilastopaja.net|date=26 January 2017|accessdate=26 January 2017}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Rank\n!Time\n!Athlete\n!Nationality\n!Date\n!Place\n!Ref\n|-\n!1\n|5.99 A\n|[[Obadele Thompson]]\n|{{flagu|Barbados}}\n|22 February 1997\n|Colorado Springs\n|\n|-\n!2\n|6.00\n|[[Lee McRae]]\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|14 March 1986\n|Oklahoma City\n|\n|-\n!3\n|6.02 A\n|[[Leo Myles-Mills]]\n|{{flagu|Ghana}}\n|22 February 1997\n|Colorado Springs\n|\n|-\n!rowspan=2|4\n|6.03\n|[[Sam Graddy]]\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|14 March 1986\n|Oklahoma City\n|\n|-\n|6.03 {{efn|name=60y|Converted from a time for the slightly shorter 60 yards by adding 0.01}}\n|[[Carl Lewis]]\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|5 February 1983\n|Dallas\n|\n|-\n!rowspan=2|6\n|6.04\n|[[Andr\u00e9 Cason]]\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|9 March 1990\n|Indianapolis\n|\n|-\n|6.04 A\n|[[Ato Boldon]]\n|{{flagu|Trinidad and Tobago}}\n|1 February 1997\n|Flagstaff\n|\n|-\n!rowspan=2|8\n|6.05\n|[[Brian Cooper (sprinter)|Brian Cooper]]\n|{{flagu|United States}}\n|13 February 1